main event: Radar operators at El Toro MCAS reported several unidentified aerial objects detected on radar on November 7, 1956.
interesting points: The unidentified targets were flying at an estimated altitude of 3,000 feet and at a speed of approximately 600 mph., They were confirmed by tower operators who observed their rapid changes in direction., Aircraft from El Toro were scrambled but could not make visual contact with the targets., The radar contact lasted for approximately 15 minutes before it was lost., Four radar scope photographs were taken during the tracking of the unidentified object.
witness description: radar operator at El Toro MCAS
